If you haven’t heard this radio transmission, please take the time to listen. ⛔️Be cautioned it is hard to listen to.⛔️

The calm voice in the chaos  in Chicago during the incident that occurred on 8/7/2021. Thank you Dispatcher Keith Thornton - The way he took control of this incident and talked to his officers, kept his air completely shut down and clear, set a perimeter within seconds quite possibly is what resulted in the apprehension of the suspects. 

Dispatcher Keith Thornton was fast thinking and took initiative without any direction in the very beginning stages and ran the emergency like an actual incident commander - far beyond the criteria of any dispatcher. 

The world heard you loud and clear and we stand with you. 💙🖤💙🖤💙🖤💙

Looks like Democrat Leadership in Portland realized they made a HUGE MISTAKE by defunding their police and dismantling its gun violence unit, which was dismantled over a year ago at the height of the Black Lives Matter movement which was calling to defund Police. 

But due to the city’s rising homicide rate Portland leadership is now backtracking on their decision to disband the unit and has moved to resurrect the Police Gun violence unit, renaming the unit as the “Focused Initiative Team."

BUT they can’t find enough officers to join.

Do you blame them? 

The once-prestigious positions on the Portland’s Gun Violence Reduction Team are now considered less desirable due to the added scrutiny that comes with the role.

They’re demonizing and vilifying you, and then they want to put you in a unit where you’re under an even bigger microscope," Daryl Turner, leader of the Portland Police Association, a union representing rank-and-file officers, told the newspaper. 

Portland has seen 53 homicides so far this year, putting it on track to pass the all-time high of 70 in 1987. As officers were redeployed to ongoing, violent demonstrations at government buildings that stretched from last summer until early this year, a sense of lawlessness grew. Neighborhood patrols suffered and officers grew more hesitant to conduct preventative investigative stops. 

Homicides have surged since the unit was disbanded last summer after the Portland City Council voted last summer to slash the police bureau’s budget by $15 million. Amid the uptick in gun violence, Mayor Ted Wheeler proposed a new unit in March renamed the "Focused Initiative Team."

node.text:
Meanwhile American Citizens are being forced to show proof of vaccination in some major cities just to go about your daily lives. This is an outrage. 

Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton on Wednesday slammed President Biden and his administration over the handling of illegal immigrants amid the pandemic, telling Fox News it was “hypocritical” and that “the credibility of the president on COVID is gone.”

Paxton said he had lost all “respect for the president” given he was releasing illegal immigrants into the community while still preaching about the importance of masks and vaccines.

“He is letting all these people in knowing they have COVID. They are being dropped off all over the country. I was talking to some Dallas police officers. They watched … a couple of buses unload in downtown Dallas in the middle of the night. These people just disappeared. Many of them have COVID.

“And to be lectured about masks and vaccines by the administration, to be told when you are out of the country and a US citizen, you can’t come back if you have COVID, is hypocritical.

“I have lost complete respect for the president on the whole COVID issue given the fact that he is allowing people to cross the border and doesn’t seem to care.”

Meanwhile, Fox News’ Tucker Carlson has revealed that a convicted illegal felon had been allowed to remain in the US by Immigration and Customs Enforcement following a request from an Abolish ICE activist.

Citing emails that he obtained, Carlson said ICE Acting Director Tae Johnson had given permission for Marvin Jerezano Pena to remain in the country after being approached by activist Tania Mattos.

Carlson claimed Pena, who has prior convictions for robbery, simple assault and drug charges, was ordered deported in July last year.

“This is what they’re doing as our border has turned into total chaos … our country is being invaded by the rest of the world — not just Mexico, not just Latin America, the whole world — and they’re worried about how they can keep a felon in our country without you knowing about it,” Carlson said, adding that ICE confirmed that Pena was not deported.
